# Deferred work

- Remove the trusted VLAN dual-stack (IPv4) once Windows CLAT ships in stable:
  repo side per the trusted_ipv4 comment in host_vars/vanguard.yml, then on
  vanguard:
    delete interfaces ethernet eth2 vif 20 address 10.0.20.1/24
    delete service dhcp-server
    delete nat source rule 1000
    delete firewall ipv4 input filter rule 1000
    delete firewall ipv4 input filter rule 1001
    delete firewall ipv4 forward filter rule 1000
  (use 'delete service dhcp-server shared-network-name trusted' instead if
  other DHCPv4 scopes exist by then)

- Create the untrusted VLAN (60) in the gateway role: internet only, no
  inter-VLAN access; intra-VLAN isolation via Proxmox per-VM firewall (and
  switch port isolation once lagrange exists)
- Deploy atlas (step-ca) and distribute its root certificate to every managed
  device

- NTP redirect rule: force IoT devices with hardcoded public NTP (pool.ntp.org)
  to use vanguard instead (outbound UDP 123 redirect)
- Tighten firewall forward rule 310 (services -> iot) to gaia's address once
  gaia exists
- Once polaris serves encrypted DNS, switch firewall forward rule 215
  (trusted -> polaris) from plaintext 53 to the TLS port (853 DoT / 443 DoH)
  and drop plaintext
- Lock down pioneer (label printer) to only the protocols it actually needs:
  restrict trusted -> pioneer to its print ports (e.g. IPP 631, raw 9100) and
  drop everything else, once the device is on the network and its real port
  usage is confirmed
- mDNS repeater between services and iot if a device needs auto-discovery
- Remove default-log from the input chain once the network is stable (keep it
  on forward)
- Configure eth1 (5G backup WAN) and WAN failover
- Managed switch: VLAN enforcement + untagged wired devices (currently wired
  devices must tag their own traffic)
- Once polaris is built: do DNS64 locally (AdGuard), point RDNSS at polaris,
  and restore Cloudflare + Google as plain upstreams
- Ship vanguard logs to hubble via remote syslog (Grafana + Loki + Alloy) and
  add the management -> services syslog firewall rule
- Consider restricting the forward ICMPv6 rule to specific types (currently
  allows ping between all VLANs)
- Replace the Proxmox API self-signed cert with an atlas-issued one and drop
  `insecure = true` from terraform/providers.tf once atlas exists
- Scope the Terraform Proxmox token to a dedicated terraform@pve user with a
  minimal custom role (privsep 1 + ACLs) instead of the root@pam privsep-0 token
